And when I ask you this, this way, do you think the guy's going to answer me?

00:56:41.019 --> 00:56:42.019
Or is he going to say, no, I'm not sharing?

00:56:42.199 --> 00:56:46.539
I'm like, okay, but if you, and you know what, by the way, if somebody comes and he's like, oh, it's confidential.

00:56:46.800 --> 00:56:47.119
I don't know.

00:56:47.742 --> 00:56:48.860
It never happened, by the way.

00:56:48.920 --> 00:56:51.960
But if he does, I'm like, how can I help you if I don't know?

00:56:55.072 --> 00:56:55.358
Make sense?

00:56:57.503 --> 00:56:59.739
So, don't be aggressive with people.

00:57:00.451 --> 00:57:00.800
Be nice.

00:57:00.940 --> 00:57:02.400
But you want them to open up?

00:57:03.188 --> 00:57:03.860
Ask them questions.

00:57:05.081 --> 00:57:07.480
And you know why I love to ask what they've done in the past?

00:57:08.565 --> 00:57:09.460
Because they're going to be screwed.

00:57:10.780 --> 00:57:16.320
Because who is making here 20%, 29% return in 12 months in average for the past four years?

00:57:17.132 --> 00:57:17.340
Nobody.

00:57:18.514 --> 00:57:18.659
Us.

00:57:20.684 --> 00:57:21.559
So, I know I have leverage.

00:57:23.061 --> 00:57:28.599
And if the person is like, yeah, sometimes they're going to be like, by the way, guys, I've been asking the question.

00:57:28.760 --> 00:57:30.193
I think the maximum I got is like 15%.

00:57:31.143 --> 00:57:32.998
All the people that are making 30%, they do everything themselves.

00:57:35.302 --> 00:57:38.480
And by the way, when they tell me that, I'm like, okay, is it before or after taxes?

00:57:40.081 --> 00:57:41.139
Oh, I invest in France.

00:57:41.300 --> 00:57:42.478
No, no, it's before taxes.

00:57:42.800 --> 00:57:44.179
At the end, I have actually 12.

00:57:45.186 --> 00:57:45.619
You know what I mean?

00:57:46.083 --> 00:57:48.300
So, you can play with that to get the net.

00:57:49.148 --> 00:57:49.659
Does that make sense?

00:57:52.306 --> 00:57:52.920
Let me give you that.

00:57:58.601 --> 00:57:59.759
People actively listening.

00:58:00.059 --> 00:58:06.079
Just so you know, guys, right now, as we speak, there's only 10% to 20% of the people that actually really listen.

00:58:06.766 --> 00:58:08.360
Some of you are checking their phone.

00:58:08.559 --> 00:58:10.260
Some of you are checking, doing something.

00:58:10.460 --> 00:58:11.719
Some of you are thinking about something else.

00:58:12.141 --> 00:58:14.019
The active listening is very, very shallow.

00:58:15.081 --> 00:58:17.820
That's why I try to do it at the beginning of the meeting.

00:58:19.081 --> 00:58:25.440
That's why I usually start the meeting with, by the way, we have about half an hour or one hour.

00:58:26.222 --> 00:58:28.579
Why don't you present yourself first for the first five minutes?

00:58:28.840 --> 00:58:30.719
I even take my phone and I put the timer on the table.

00:58:32.389 --> 00:58:32.780
You know why?

00:58:33.079 --> 00:58:36.380
Because that tells, and sometimes they see it, sometimes they don't.

00:58:36.782 --> 00:58:39.039
But I put the timer and then I present.

00:58:39.724 --> 00:58:40.559
But I let them talk.

