01:00:16.846 --> 01:00:17.599
They didn't tell me this.

01:00:18.342 --> 01:00:22.159
But by asking the question, you know, you can go very deep.

01:00:24.360 --> 01:00:28.639
Anyway, so this is where you need to be, just so you guys know.

01:00:30.161 --> 01:00:33.438
The average guy, he speaks 60% of the time.

01:00:33.980 --> 01:00:34.530
He listens 40%.

01:00:35.063 --> 01:00:35.599
That's the average.

01:00:35.780 --> 01:00:36.800
That's the guy you don't want to be.

01:00:37.541 --> 01:00:39.275
The top performer is you listen 70%.

01:00:41.222 --> 01:00:42.413
And you talk only 30%.

01:00:43.722 --> 01:00:46.400
So if you don't know how to call, just measure yourself.

01:00:48.306 --> 01:00:48.858
You will love it.

01:00:49.181 --> 01:00:49.896
I swear, this is...

01:00:50.081 --> 01:00:50.237
Yes?

01:00:50.682 --> 01:00:52.380
Just one thing about that.

01:00:52.679 --> 01:00:52.797
Yeah?

01:00:53.860 --> 01:00:56.436
Sometimes you have people, they love to talk and they change.

01:00:57.483 --> 01:00:57.858
Subject.

01:00:58.443 --> 01:00:58.960
It's crazy.

01:00:59.280 --> 01:00:59.373
Yes.

01:00:59.639 --> 01:01:02.719
You have to make them come back to the path.

01:01:02.922 --> 01:01:03.480
True, true.

01:01:03.902 --> 01:01:06.175
This is part of...

01:01:09.240 --> 01:01:11.798
That's why I start with...

01:01:12.668 --> 01:01:13.460
We have about an hour.

01:01:14.324 --> 01:01:16.059
We have about 30 minutes and I try to...

01:01:16.659 --> 01:01:16.820
You forget it.

01:01:16.981 --> 01:01:18.380
Yeah, at some point you need...

01:01:18.422 --> 01:01:18.878
It depends...

01:01:19.021 --> 01:01:21.139
Guys, it depends on how it is.

01:01:21.561 --> 01:01:25.800
But also, if they keep talking about nonsense, at some point I'm like, you know, let's go

01:01:25.860 --> 01:01:27.000
back to the subject at some point.

01:01:27.403 --> 01:01:28.239
You have to do it, right?

01:01:29.445 --> 01:01:29.614
Um...

01:01:29.840 --> 01:01:33.960
But, again, one of the things that I say, I can...

01:01:34.327 --> 01:01:34.800
I also...

01:01:34.860 --> 01:01:37.179
If the guy is like this, um...

01:01:37.342 --> 01:01:38.474
I'm also gonna ask...

01:01:39.282 --> 01:01:40.360
I just have three questions.

01:01:41.123 --> 01:01:42.476
I just need to answer me by a number.

01:01:44.001 --> 01:01:47.099
I ask my question, they answer me, I ask my second question, and then they go.

01:01:47.460 --> 01:01:47.579
You know?

01:01:47.862 --> 01:01:48.418
But I have the info.

01:01:50.081 --> 01:01:52.820
Usually, it's like the qualification question is like four to five.

01:01:53.123 --> 01:01:53.699
I will go through it.

01:01:53.940 --> 01:01:55.780
I will prepare the listing of questions.

01:01:55.981 --> 01:01:57.440
No, the questions are always the same.

01:01:57.519 --> 01:01:58.219
That's why it's beautiful.

01:01:58.541 --> 01:01:59.300
I'm gonna go through it.

01:01:59.442 --> 01:02:00.739
I'm gonna give you my question that I ask.

01:02:01.340 --> 01:02:05.559
But sometimes, obviously, it depends, you know, of the situation.

01:02:07.221 --> 01:02:07.389
Um...

01:02:07.902 --> 01:02:09.300
If someone is selling his company...

01:02:10.260 --> 01:02:12.117
Yash, we had this meeting with this, uh...

01:02:13.043 --> 01:02:14.300
Okay, remember that meeting?

01:02:14.539 --> 01:02:16.500
Okay, Yash just introduced us to a billionaire, Indian.

01:02:16.840 --> 01:02:16.976
Okay?

01:02:17.481 --> 01:02:20.119
Actually, uh, we're about to close maybe one of the villa.

01:02:20.521 --> 01:02:22.559
The guy can start with ten, he can go to a hundred million dollars.

01:02:23.041 --> 01:02:24.460
You remember that meeting when we started?

01:02:25.346 --> 01:02:26.219
How many times I spoke?

01:02:27.509 --> 01:02:28.539
Barely.

01:02:28.539 --> 01:02:30.500
How long they spoke before we really got into the subject?

01:02:31.987 --> 01:02:32.340
After what?

01:02:32.885 --> 01:02:33.259
Forty minutes.

01:02:33.461 --> 01:02:34.219
After forty minutes.

01:02:35.141 --> 01:02:37.579
How many questions I asked that have nothing to do with Real Estate

01:02:37.802 --> 01:02:39.400
and only concerning his business?

01:02:40.545 --> 01:02:40.735
Remember?

01:02:41.188 --> 01:02:41.480
Oh, yeah.

01:02:41.619 --> 01:02:41.900
Basically.

01:02:42.643 --> 01:02:44.340
He was like, I sold my business.

01:02:44.440 --> 01:02:45.539
Oh, I'm like, oh, that's interesting.

01:02:45.844 --> 01:02:46.539
How much was it?

01:02:47.800 --> 01:02:48.032
Um...

01:02:48.242 --> 01:02:48.760
What did you do?

01:02:49.344 --> 01:02:49.940
What did you sell?

01:02:50.583 --> 01:02:51.800
Uh, you know, I got interested.

01:02:52.019 --> 01:02:52.659
I got him to give.

01:02:53.041 --> 01:02:54.880
And you know, people love to talk about what they are doing

01:02:55.003 --> 01:02:55.519
or what they've done.

01:02:56.422 --> 01:02:57.960
And then the guy started to open up.

01:02:58.592 --> 01:02:59.538
Open up.

01:03:00.224 --> 01:03:01.659
And ask even some mentoring questions.

01:03:02.599 --> 01:03:07.820
I'm like, you know, if you were me, what would you do?

01:03:09.063 --> 01:03:11.000
Um, you know, like, oh, I like this.

01:03:11.179 --> 01:03:11.340
Whatever.

01:03:11.842 --> 01:03:16.059
So, sometimes you need to, if you see that the person is also very successful

01:03:17.103 --> 01:03:19.400
and he has potentially a lot of money to put with you.

01:03:19.820 --> 01:03:24.260
And by the way, it's not by being, um, uh, unauthentic.

01:03:24.603 --> 01:03:25.719
I'm a very authentic person.

01:03:26.161 --> 01:03:29.380
If you don't care about the people you're going to be dealing with or working with,

01:03:30.079 --> 01:03:32.579
you're going to fail at raising a lot of money.

01:03:33.222 --> 01:03:35.539
It's not like I'm here to ask questions because I want his money.

01:03:35.639 --> 01:03:40.980
No, I'm also genuinely interested to ask the question for the guy to open up.

01:03:41.681 --> 01:03:45.500
And at the, at that point, at the end, when the guy opened up, I'm like, okay, how much

01:03:45.539 --> 01:03:47.199
would you be interested to invest?

01:03:47.889 --> 01:03:48.679
He gave me the number.

01:03:50.202 --> 01:03:53.199
He gave me the number because he, he felt comfortable about it.

01:03:53.963 --> 01:03:54.074
Okay.

01:03:54.320 --> 01:04:02.079
So qualification buyer mode, buyer model, guys, this is, you cannot succeed by getting offers

01:04:02.688 --> 01:04:03.358
if you don't do this.

01:04:04.155 --> 01:04:04.260
Okay.

01:04:04.400 --> 01:04:10.079
So the nationality is just, this is my template that I like to ask my brokers to send me the,

01:04:10.161 --> 01:04:10.860
the, the information.

01:04:11.721 --> 01:04:16.679
So the buyer nationality, because it tells me also some indication about how bad or,

01:04:17.059 --> 01:04:21.400
how easy is potentially be the negotiation, you know, without prejudices.

01:04:21.760 --> 01:04:24.980
People, I like to also know the minimum number of bedroom.

01:04:26.541 --> 01:04:28.480
Some people, you don't ask this question.

01:04:29.003 --> 01:04:30.320
Who asked this question all the time?

01:04:30.521 --> 01:04:31.380
I asked this question all the time.

01:04:31.480 --> 01:04:32.159
Why minimum number?

01:04:32.599 --> 01:04:37.820
So, because, and also what I, what I used to love to do is like, oh, I'm looking for six bedroom.

01:04:39.427 --> 01:04:39.878
Uh, okay.

01:04:40.402 --> 01:04:42.860
But if I didn't find you, I used to love this line so much.

01:04:42.960 --> 01:04:49.239
Look, if I find you the perfect villa within your budget with five bedroom, you would not buy it.

01:04:49.400 --> 01:04:49.500
Right?

01:04:50.684 --> 01:04:51.280
No five bedroom.

01:04:52.005 --> 01:04:52.599
Actually I could.

01:04:53.842 --> 01:04:56.340
But if I find you the perfect house with four bedroom, would you buy it?

01:04:56.460 --> 01:04:58.840
No, I really need five bedroom, five to six bedroom.

01:04:59.262 --> 01:05:00.159
So it's not a six bedroom.

01:05:00.340 --> 01:05:01.119
It's a five to six.

01:05:01.543 --> 01:05:03.159
And I do that with all of those points.

01:05:03.880 --> 01:05:04.940
Minimum number of bedroom.

01:05:06.221 --> 01:05:07.559
Ideal and maximum moving date.

01:05:07.900 --> 01:05:09.639
Why do I ask maximum moving date?

01:05:10.744 --> 01:05:12.400
I want to know what's your ideal moving date.

01:05:12.559 --> 01:05:12.679
Okay.

01:05:13.021 --> 01:05:14.039
One month, two months, three months.

01:05:14.400 --> 01:05:16.880
But my maximum is that time.

01:05:18.141 --> 01:05:21.179
Because I can play with it for terms and conditions.

01:05:21.742 --> 01:05:22.579
We're going to talk about that.

01:05:23.639 --> 01:05:24.880
Maximum and ideal budget.

01:05:25.362 --> 01:05:27.739
Just people, they ask, okay, how much do you have to invest?

01:05:28.605 --> 01:05:29.900
Uh, this is for buying a property.

01:05:30.445 --> 01:05:31.099
What's your budget?

01:05:31.561 --> 01:05:33.559
People are going to tell you the real budget.

01:05:33.909 --> 01:05:34.257
They won't.

01:05:35.402 --> 01:05:38.460
But if you ask, what's your ideal budget?

01:05:40.179 --> 01:05:47.480
Or sometimes the best question is, how much do you want max, you know,

01:05:47.800 --> 01:05:50.659
do you ideally want to spend to buy your villa?

01:05:51.342 --> 01:05:53.840
Because sometimes you can be a bit offending when you ask the question,

01:05:54.684 --> 01:05:55.420
what's your budget?

01:05:55.981 --> 01:05:59.318
They may have a billion dollars, but they may want to spend only 50 million dollars.

01:06:00.182 --> 01:06:01.920
So it's not like, you know what I'm saying?

01:06:02.143 --> 01:06:02.840
You don't want to be insulting.

01:06:03.041 --> 01:06:07.079
So you can say, what's your ideal amount of money you would like to invest?

01:06:07.322 --> 01:06:08.400
I asked that to the Brazilian.

01:06:08.740 --> 01:06:10.280
He told me, 20 million dollars.

01:06:10.719 --> 01:06:10.998
Ideally.

01:06:11.804 --> 01:06:12.358
What's the max?

01:06:14.525 --> 01:06:15.460
35 million dollars.

01:06:16.121 --> 01:06:16.980
You know what happened next?

01:06:17.360 --> 01:06:23.480
I'm like, what if I give you the perfect villa that you want for 50 million dollars?

01:06:23.719 --> 01:06:24.318
Would you buy it?

01:06:25.842 --> 01:06:27.679
50, I can stretch, but that's my maximum.

01:06:27.884 --> 01:06:28.759
Something like that came up.

01:06:30.371 --> 01:06:30.559
Perfect.

01:06:30.860 --> 01:06:31.858
I know the maximum is 50.

01:06:32.119 --> 01:06:34.679
If you just stop at, what's your budget?

01:06:35.184 --> 01:06:35.956
The guy's like 20.

01:06:37.103 --> 01:06:37.860
You're going to lose.

01:06:38.762 --> 01:06:40.679
Because you didn't ask the two parts of the question.

01:06:40.880 --> 01:06:41.978
The ideal and the maximum.

01:06:44.246 --> 01:06:45.239
The desired location.

01:06:45.900 --> 01:06:48.400
Some people, okay, which location are you looking for?

01:06:49.005 --> 01:06:50.360
Oh, I only look in Jumeirah Island.

01:06:51.010 --> 01:06:51.300
Oh, really?

01:06:52.050 --> 01:06:52.179
Okay.

01:06:52.581 --> 01:06:54.679
If I find you a house in Emirates Hills, you would not buy it?

01:06:55.882 --> 01:06:56.820
Yes, actually I would buy it.

01:06:57.282 --> 01:06:57.880
Tilal Al Gaf?

01:06:58.063 --> 01:06:58.619
No, it's too far.

01:06:59.224 --> 01:06:59.659
Al Bahari?

