By the way, we're all both.

01:37:06.865 --> 01:37:07.600
But do you guys know?

01:37:08.521 --> 01:37:11.640
I don't know if you noticed, but Guillaume and me, we work very differently.

01:37:12.980 --> 01:37:15.899
Guillaume is very focused on numbers and logic and no emotion.

01:37:16.822 --> 01:37:19.399
I'm more on the emotional side, but I have the logic as well.

01:37:19.479 --> 01:37:20.220
You need to sell both.

01:37:20.600 --> 01:37:23.020
By the way, a logical person, you need to sell them with numbers.

01:37:24.921 --> 01:37:27.520
When somebody starts, you know those people that talk to you forever?

01:37:27.780 --> 01:37:28.699
You need to tell them stories.

01:37:30.103 --> 01:37:31.880
The people with the numbers, you need to go back with the numbers.

01:37:31.880 --> 01:37:32.960
I'm just sharing with you.

01:37:33.079 --> 01:37:34.560
So that's why I do the three of them.

01:37:34.902 --> 01:37:36.899
So I speak to all of their brain.

01:37:40.423 --> 01:37:41.539
There is a technique called AIDA.

01:37:41.600 --> 01:37:42.300
I don't know if you guys know.

01:37:42.724 --> 01:37:43.859
The first thing is attention.

01:37:43.880 --> 01:37:44.958
You need to catch their attention.

01:37:45.743 --> 01:37:47.119
The second is the interest.

01:37:47.319 --> 01:37:48.439
Okay, I'm interested to invest.

01:37:48.981 --> 01:37:51.119
Then from interest, the next one is desire.

01:37:51.340 --> 01:37:53.119
Okay, how much would you like to invest?

01:37:53.279 --> 01:37:54.560
And are you willing to invest?

01:37:54.699 --> 01:37:56.039
And then action, they're going to close.

01:37:56.681 --> 01:37:58.520
This cannot happen in one go, guys.

01:37:59.162 --> 01:38:01.520
When you meet an investor, when you need even a buyer.

01:38:02.021 --> 01:38:05.840
It's very rare that you have one guy, he's like this, and I'm sold on the spot.

01:38:06.484 --> 01:38:07.720
So that's why we do a process.

01:38:08.702 --> 01:38:11.220
So to engage with them, teaser, key data, video.

01:38:12.525 --> 01:38:13.100
Ways to engage.

01:38:13.462 --> 01:38:14.359
Did you already invest it?

01:38:14.539 --> 01:38:18.159
Do you know anyone who would be interested to invest a million plus, 10 million plus?

01:38:18.740 --> 01:38:23.119
By the way, let's say you want to talk to someone that is a big whale, 10 million plus.

01:38:23.824 --> 01:38:25.899
But you have a good relationship with that person.

01:38:26.583 --> 01:38:27.640
You don't want to pitch him directly.

01:38:28.384 --> 01:38:29.819
The best pitch is indirect pitch.

01:38:30.444 --> 01:38:31.439
Best pitch is indirect pitch.

01:38:32.582 --> 01:38:33.720
So how do you do it?

01:38:34.162 --> 01:38:35.159
This guy is a 10 million dollar guy.

01:38:35.301 --> 01:38:35.979
Hey, Johnny.

01:38:38.122 --> 01:38:40.880
You know what I do with Green Bull, what we've done, you know, all of this.

01:38:41.961 --> 01:38:45.619
Do you know two or three people on the top of your head right now that you can recommend

01:38:45.699 --> 01:38:49.239
that would be interested to invest 10 to 100 million dollars in real estate?

01:38:50.407 --> 01:38:50.838
Let me think.

01:38:53.042 --> 01:38:55.239
Most of the time, he's going to say, yeah, I might be interested.

01:38:55.460 --> 01:38:58.640
But at the end, you reserve, you reverse the trend.

01:38:59.041 --> 01:38:59.939
People hate being sold.

01:39:00.521 --> 01:39:04.838
If you call Johnny and like, hey, Johnny, would you like to invest 10 to 100?

01:39:05.404 --> 01:39:06.359
Yeah, send me the deck, whatever.

01:39:06.840 --> 01:39:11.859
If you do the indirect, not only he's going to give you referral, but also he might be interested

01:39:12.027 --> 01:39:12.319
himself.

01:39:12.764 --> 01:39:13.579
But it's a reverse thing.

01:39:13.739 --> 01:39:15.880
You didn't think about him because you didn't ask him directly.

01:39:16.320 --> 01:39:16.939
Does that make sense?

01:39:17.824 --> 01:39:18.599
This is so powerful.

01:39:19.324 --> 01:39:19.699
So powerful.

